whereas.text:
Whereas in both the United States and Russia, the number
			 of children in need of loving parents far outnumbers the families actively
			 seeking to adopt;

Whereas in 19 cases, adopted Russian children have died
			 from abuse or neglect in the care of their adoptive United States parents, and
			 others have suffered abuse;

Whereas countries making children available for
			 international adoption have the right and responsibility to set procedural
			 safeguards and criteria to ensure the children’s well-being;

paragraph.text:
appeals to the
			 Russian Government to allow the adoptions initiated before January 1, 2013, to
			 proceed to conclusion;

invites the
			 Government of Russia to continue participation in the bilateral adoption
			 agreement that went into force November 1, 2012;

expresses deep sadness over the untimely
			 and tragic deaths in the United States of 19 adopted Russian children and over
			 the other cases of abuse;

celebrates the
			 tens of thousands of loving, safe United States families who have opened their
			 homes and hearts to Russian children;
